        "last_played": 1387852545
      },
      "language": "english",
      "review": "This game is seriously fun.  It is very well made, and has beautiful graphics.  While it is a bridge building game, I'm not lying when I tell you it is intense and insane at times.  I have literally yelled at my computer several times when I was only a segment away from making my bridge work with trucks, but it was worth it. \n\nWhile it appears simplistic, it feels realistic.  Although realistic it provides the perfect amount of goofyness to the game to keep me relaxed after my yelling.  The goofyness does nothing to detract from the gameplay, and only adds to it.  I can not express how much I love to play it.\n\nOnly downside is the musical tracks, which pretty much becomes ambient after a while, which really makes it not a problem.\n\nOverall I give it a 9.5/10 due to the linear/limited gameplay aspect of it, but other than that, very well polished and well worth the money spent.  \n\nI can dream for a sandbox bridge mode, right ;)?",
